Percocypris pingi is a species of cyprinid in the genus Percocypris. It inhabits Yunnan, China and possibly Laos and Myanmar. Assessed as near threatened on the IUCN Red List, it has a decreasing population. It has a maximum length of 44.0 centimetres (17.3 in) and is considered harmless to humans. It is used for food both locally and nationally.